The paper deals with modeling and analyzing communication channels, specifically Transmission Line (TL) based channels, which are commonly studied in the Information Theory (IT) and Signal Processing (SP) communities. The paper also discusses the use of Lifting and Trailing Zeros (L&TZ) techniques, which are commonly used in System Theory (SY) and Circuit Analysis (COM). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the proposed methodology to Time Varying (TV) systems, which is relevant to the Networked Systems (NI) community. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.SP, cs.COMM, and cs.NI.
